<div class="min-h-screen pt-14 pb-10 relative" style="background: transparent;">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
    <div class="mb-6">
      <%= link_to root_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 btn btn-secondary group" do %>
        <span class="material-icons transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform">arrow_back</span>
        <span>Back to Home</span>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <article class="glass-thick rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12">
      <header class="mb-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Currently Reading</h1>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <section>
          <div class="grid gap-6">
            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "Staff Engineer: Leadership beyond the management track", 
                    "https://www.amazon.com/Staff-Engineer-Leadership-beyond-management/dp/1736417916",
                    target: "_blank", 
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                I'm diving deep into Will Larson's guide on technical leadership. As someone who's been thinking about the staff engineer path, this book has been eye-opening about how to grow your impact without necessarily going the management route.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "The Rails 8 Way",
                    "https://leanpub.com/therails8way",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer", 
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                Obie's back with the Rails 8 edition. I'm particularly interested in the Hotwire coverage and how SQLite is becoming a production-ready option. The framework keeps evolving in fascinating ways.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "Designing Data-Intensive Applications",
                    "https://www.amazon.com/Designing-Data-Intensive-Applications-Reliable-Maintainable/dp/1449373321",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                Kleppmann's book is dense but worth it. I'm working through the distributed systems chapters now - it's changing how I think about data consistency and system architecture at scale.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Fiction & Personal Growth</h2>
          <div class="grid gap-6">
            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "The Ministry of Time",
                    "https://www.amazon.com/Ministry-Time-Novel-Kaliane-Bradley/dp/1668045141",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                Just started this time-travel spy romance that everyone's been raving about. Sometimes you need a good fiction break from all the technical reading. Plus, the BBC is adapting it!
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

